## Introduction

Cub3D is a raycasting game written in C. This project uses the raycasting technique to create a simple 3D world using a 2D map. It was originally developed as a Wolfenstein 3D by id Software in 1992.

## Features

- Raycasting engine
- 3D rendering
- Map parsing

## Dependencies

- lbsd

## Getting Started

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/teoet/cub3d.git
cd cub3d

## Building and Running

```bash
# Build the project
make

# Run the game
./cub3D resources/maps/map.cub
```
## Controls

- W: Move forward
- A: Move left
- S: Move backward
- D: Move right
 Use arrow keys to move the camera.
